        <subsection xml:id="Question_2_5_3">
    <title> Problem 3</title>
<ol marker="(a)">

    <li>
        <p>
        <m>(18,5)=1</m>,  <m>2 \cdot 18 -7\cdot 5=1</m>, <m>96\cdot 18-336\cdot 5=48</m>
        The general solution is:
        <md>
            <mrow>x \amp =96+5t</mrow>
            <mrow>y \amp = -336-18t</mrow>
        </md>

        If we want <md>
            <mrow>96+5t \amp &gt; 0 \text{ and}</mrow>
            <mrow> -336-18t \amp &gt; 0 </mrow>
        </md>
        or 
        <md>
            <mrow> t \amp &gt; -\frac{96}{5} \text{and}</mrow>
            <mrow>t \amp  &lt; -\frac{336}{18}.</mrow>
        </md>
        
        So, only <m>t=-19</m> gives a positive solution:
        <md>
            <mrow>x \amp = 96-19\cdot 5=1 \text{ and} </mrow>
            <mrow> y \amp= -336-18(-19)=6</mrow>
        </md>
        
        

        </p>
    </li>
</ol>
</subsection>



        <subsection xml:id="Question_2_5_6">
    <title> Problem 6</title>

    <p> From the total number of livestock:
        <md>
            c+l+p=100
        </md>
From the cost information:
        <md>
            120c+50l+25p=4000
        </md>
        Solve for <m>c</m>:
        <md>
            c=100-l-p
        </md>
Combine the two equations and simplify:
        <md>
            <mrow>120(100-l-p)+50l+25p \amp = 4000</mrow>
            <mrow> 12000-120l-120p+50l+25p \amp = 4000  </mrow>
            <mrow>8000 \amp = 70l +95p  </mrow>
        </md>
Find one solution to the Diophantine equation:
        <md>
           <mrow> -4\cdot 70 + 3 \cdot 95 \amp =5 </mrow>
           <mrow>-6400\cdot 70 +4800 \cdot 95 \amp = 8000 </mrow>
        </md>
        The general solution for <m>l</m> and <m>p</m> is:
        <md>
            <mrow>l \amp =-6400+\frac{95}{5}t </mrow>
            <mrow> p \amp = 4800 -\frac{70}{5}t </mrow>
        </md>
        
        or 

         <md>
            <mrow>l \amp =-6400+19t </mrow>
            <mrow> p \amp = 4800 -14t </mrow>
        </md>
        
        These are both postive if <m>t=337, 338, 339, 340, 341, 342</m>.

        If you compute the resulting number of calves for each of these cases you'll find that <m>t=337, 338, 339</m> also give a positive number of calves.  So, there are 3 possible answers to the question.
    </p>
    </subsection>


